Keep the aesthetic of the ceramic vessel, but alter the composition to include the figures mentioned above. Weave these new figures into the current scenery so that the original elements and the new scene coexist naturally.

All figures in the scene are strictly nude, masculine males with idealized, classically Roman features and muscular anatomy. The figures represent virility and physical perfection. Avoid long hair or other characteristics that could read feminine. The scene is dynamic, depicting the figures in visually interesting and appealing poses.

Maintain the artwork style and vessel form from the uploaded image in the newly created scenery.

Ensure all edits are seamlessly integrated with the existing artwork. Colors must be harmonious with the original palette, and surrounding imagery and elements must flow naturally without making the new scene stand out as an obvious edit. Subtly echo decorative motifs, border patterns, and stylistic elements from the existing vessel in the edited sections to create visual continuity and coherence.

The negative space around the new scenery must be harmonious with the existing vessel, ensuring sufficient negative space for the piece to feel elegant. the male figures are surrounded by a bit of empty space to make them more prominent as the subject of the image. If new elements overlap or interact with existing elements, the integration must be seamless and thoughtful.

